  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Altair JSON Placeholder</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.7.2/css/all.min.css"
      integrity="sha512-Evv84Mr4kqVGRNSgIGL/F/aIDqQb7xQ2vcrdIwxfjThSH8CSR7PBEakCr51Ck+w+/U6swU2Im1vVX0SVk9ABhg=="
      crossorigin="anonymous"
      referrerpolicy="no-referrer"
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/imgs/favicon.ico" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <div class="hero">
        <h1>Welcome to Altair JSON Placeholder</h1>
        <p>
          Altair JSON Placeholder is a free online REST API that provides fake
          data for testing and prototyping. Use it for your front-end, back-end,
          or mobile app development. All the API Data is hardcoded and looks
          realistic, making it ideal for testing purposes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="">Available API Endpoints</h2>
      <div class="endpoints">
        <div class="box">
          <h2>Users</h2>
          <p>Get all users or a specific user by ID.</p>
          <p><a href="/users">/users</a>, <a href="/users/1">/users/{id}</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
          <h2>Posts</h2>
          <p>Retrieve all posts or a specific post.</p>
          <p><a href="/posts">/posts</a>, <a href="/posts/1">/posts/{id}</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
          <h2>Todos</h2>
          <p>Fetch all to-dos or a specific to-do.</p>
          <p><a href="/todos">/todos</a>, <a href="/todos/1">/todos/{id}</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
          <h2>Comments</h2>
          <p>Get various post comments.</p>
          <p>
            <a href="/comments">/comments</a>,
            <a href="/comments/1">/comments/{id}</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="error-section">
        <h2>Error Simulations</h2>
        <p>We provide various error simulations for testing:</p>
        <p><a href="/simulate/404">/404</a> - Not Found</p>
        <p><a href="/simulate/429">/429</a> - Too Many Requests</p>
        <p><a href="/simulate/500">/500</a> - Internal Server Error</p>
      </div>

      <div class="error-section">
        <h2>HTTP Methods Support</h2>
        <p>
          Our API supports all 5 HTTP request types for full testing:
          <strong>GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE.</strong>
        </p>
        <div class="row">
          <span>GET</span>
          <a href="/request/">/request</a>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <span>POST</span>
          <a>/request</a>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <span>DELETE</span>
          <a>/request</a>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <span>PUT</span>
          <a>/request</a>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <span>PATCH</span>
          <a>/request</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="auth-section">
        <h2>Authentication Endpoints</h2>
        <p>
          Our API includes authentication endpoints for testing login,
          registration, and logout functionalities.
        </p>

        <div class="boxes">
          <div class="auth-box">
            <h3>Login</h3>
            <p>Authenticate a user using email and password.</p>
            <p>
              <strong>Method:</strong> POST <br />
              <strong>URL:</strong> <a href="/auth/login/">/login/</a>
            </p>
            <pre>
{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
          </pre
            >
          </div>

          <div class="auth-box">
            <h3>Register</h3>
            <p>Create a new user account.</p>
            <p>
              <strong>Method:</strong> POST <br />
              <strong>URL:</strong> <a href="/auth/register/">/register/</a>
            </p>
            <pre>
{
  "username": "JohnDoe",
  "email": "johndoe@example.com",
  "password": "securePass123",
  "confirmPassword": "securePass123"
}
          </pre
            >
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="auth-box">
          <h3>Logout</h3>
          <p>Logout a user.</p>
          <p>
            <strong>Method:</strong> POST <br />
            <strong>URL:</strong> <a href="/auth/logout/">/logout/</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>

